         MACRO
&NAME    FINDSYM &A
.* THIS MACRO MAY BE USED WHENEVER A SYMBOLIC NAME IS REQUIRED
.*   TO BE FOUND IN THE SYMBOLIC PARAMETER TABLE.
.*
.* MODIFIED BY C. CLARKE, MAY, 1987 FOR BINARY SEARCH ROUTINES.
.*
.* IT IS ASSUMED THAT 'JOLCOM' IS ADDRESSABLE.
.*
.* THE PARAMETER MAY BE A REGISTER NOTATION, INDICATING THAT THE
.*   REGISTER IS A POINTER TO THE VARIABLE CONTAING THE NAME
.*   WE ARE TO LOOK FOR, OR
.*   THE PARAMETER MAY BE A LOCATION CONTAINING THE NAME.
.*
.* AN 8 BYTE NAME IS ALWAYS SEARCHED FOR.
.*
.*
&NAME    LA    R1,&A          ADDRESS OF SYMBOL WE NEED
         $CALL UJPFSYM        SEARCH TABLE, RETN 0 OR 4
         MEND
